@Node "Usage"

    @{b}Configuration file@{plain}

    Sniffy reads its configuration from a text file.
    In parsing it, there are ignored:
    - empty lines
    - lines starting with # or ;
    - chars after the 256th
    - chars after # or ;
    - lines after the 256th

    Each lines consist of
    OPTION {ARGUMENT}

    Valid options are:
    - LOG <file> the Sniffy log file.

    - CX_POPKEY <hotkey> keys-sequence description to open the gui

    - FILTER <filter> "," <macro> "," <flags>
             defines a filter:
             - filter string in pcap format
             - macro  complete macro name to call
                      extension is "sniffy"
                      host is SNIFFY.X
             - flags are one or more of
               - NTDOMACRO don't call the macro, if present, for this filter
               - SYSLOG
               - SNIFFYLOG



    @{b}Filters@{plain}

    Sniffy filters are string in pcap format.
    E.g. "tcp and dst port 12345" to filter a NetBus connection
         "udp and dst port 31337" to filter a BackOrifice packet



    @{b}Macros@{plain}

    Macros are called with arguments:

    1. the protocol number
    2. the source host in dotted form
    3. the dest host in dotted form
    4. the packet len
    5. the packet (as visible to tcp/ip)

    So the macro can read its arguments with a statement like

    /**/
    parse arg proto,src,dst,len,pkt
    ...

    and can do what it wants with them.

    Of course, having @{"rxsocket.library" rxs "call addlib('rmh.library',0,-30);call openurl('http://users.iol.it/alfier/soft/rxsocket.html')"} installed helps very much
    in packets parsing.

    Sniffy doesn't care about macros results and if the macro does exist or not.



    @{b}Usage@{plain}

    Sniffy can be run from shell with template:

    DEVICE,CONFIG/K,PUBSCREEN/K,ACTIVE/S,NOGUI/S,CX_POPKEY/K,CX_PRIORITY/K/N:

    DEVICE     name of the interface to monitor;
               if none the first interface "NOT LOOPBACK AND UP" (suitable) is used

    CONFIG     name of the configuration file; default is Sniffy.conf

    ACTIVE     go active

    NOGUI      don't open the gui, all gui resources are not opened

    CX_POPKEY  keys-sequence description to open the gui
               without the "="

    CXPRIORYTY commodity priority
               without the "="

    Sniffy can be run from Workbench with the same Tooltypes
    as in shell template.



    @{b}Windows@{plain}

    Sniffy gui consists of 3 windows:

    - main window

      - Menů

        - Project
          - Play dump...  *not implemeted yet*
          - About...      open the About window
          - Hide          iconify and free all gui resources
          - Quit          quit Sniffy

        - Editor
          - Config...     open the configuration window
          - Read IF List  read the active interfaces list
          - Help          set help mode on: in the status
                          gadget will be show the help of
                          the gadget below the mouse
      - Gadgets
        - Interface     the interface to sniffy
        - PopInterface  show the avaible interface(s)
        - Dump          open, close a dump file.
                        A dump file is a file in a
                        format miamitcp can play back.
                        It is opened only when Sniffy goes
                        active or asap if Sniffy is already
                        active.
        - Status        show status and error messages
        - Active        start
        - Conf          open the configuration window
        - Hide          iconify and free all gui resources
        - Quit          quit Sniffy

    - Configuration window

      - Menů
        - Project
          - Open...     open a configuration file
          - Save        save this configuration
          - Save as...  save this configuration with a different name
          - Use         use this configuration
          - Quit        exit

        - Editor
          - Last Saved  load last saved configuration
          - Restore     load last used configuration

      - Gadgets
         - Filters list divided in
           - state column
             - N this filter is not compiled
             - D this filter is disabled (double click to switch it)
           - filter column filter string in pcap format
           - macro  column macro to run
         - down       move selected filter down
         - up         selected filter up
         - Filter     filter string in pcap format
         - Macro      macro to run
         - DoMacro    call the macro for this filter
         - SysLog     this filter is to be logged in syslog
         - SniffyLog  this filter is to be logged in sniffylog
         - Add        add an empty filter
         - Del        delete the selected filter
         - Copy       copy the selected filter
         - SniffyLog  the Sniffy log file, e.g. CON:0/0/640/50/Sniffy log/AUTO/CLOSE
         - Hotkey     keys-sequence description to open the gui
         - Save       save this configuration
         - Use        use this configuration
         - Cancel     exit without save

    - About window

      It consists in 4 pages of copyright info and greets.
      The ">Browser" button opens your browser and works if
      and only if you have OpenURL installed in your system.
@EndNode

@Node "ARexx"

    Sniffy opens a pubblic ARexx port.

    Valid commands to send to it are:
    - LOG    <msg> log msg in Sniffy log
    - QUIT   quit Sniffy
    - SHOW   open the gui
    - HIDE   hide the gui and free all gui resources
    - FILTER filter,macro,flags
             flags are one or more of
             - NTDOMACRO don't call the macro, if present, for this filter
             - SYSLOG
             - SNIFFYLOG
    - GOACTIVE   activate Sniffy
    - GOINACTIVE de-activate Sniffy
@EndNode

